2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 136
BY SENATOR HARRIS
ECONOMIC DEVELOP DEPT. Requests Louisiana Economic Development to study and
report on the riverfront and adjacent neighborhoods and districts in Orleans Parish.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request Louisiana Economic Development to study and report on the
3 governance, financing, jurisdiction, duties, coordination, transparency, and
4 public-benefit obligations of boards, commissions, districts, authorities, and related
5 public or quasi-public entities operating on, adjacent to, or materially affecting the
6 riverfront and adjacent neighborhoods and districts in Orleans Parish.
7 WHEREAS, the Mississippi Riverfront includes public land in Orleans Parish that
8 is historic and is among the most significant public, economic, cultural, historic,
9 transportation, and tourism assets in the state; and
10 WHEREAS, these public lands preserve historic landscapes and offer abundant
11 tourism and opportunities that draw millions of visitors annually stimulating local and state
12 economies while offering social and recreational opportunities and benefits to residents; and
13 WHEREAS, there is a need and desire to support efforts to develop, to provide and
14 encourage public access, and to coordinate through responsible and sustainable stewardship
15 of these assets; and
16 WHEREAS, the riverfront and adjacent neighborhoods and districts in Orleans Parish
17 are supported by multiple boards, commissions, districts, authorities, and related public or
18 quasi-public entities that play integral roles, with differing legal authorities, geographic
