1 boundaries, governance structures, revenue streams, operational duties, and public
2 responsibilities that often cross boundary management; and
3 WHEREAS, consultation, coordination, and alignment of the roles and
4 responsibilities between the multiple entities along the riverfront and adjacent
5 neighborhoods and districts in Orleans Parish, is essential to the long term economic vitality
6 of further economic development, tourism and recreation of the riverfront assets, the city of
7 New Orleans, and the state of Louisiana; and
8 WHEREAS, there is an interest in ensuring that the stewardship of public assets
9 along the riverfront and adjacent neighborhoods and districts in Orleans Parish are well
10 maintained, and that public entities collaborate for increased efficiency and transparency
11 ensuring that maintenance and operational cost, public safety, investment in public
12 infrastructure, governance and investment to enhance the economic, cultural, and social
13 vitality of the areas are transparent, efficient, publicly accountable, and structured in a
14 manner that supports sound stewardship of public assets, coordination, cooperation,
15 understanding of capacity, and the delivery of measurable economic and public benefit.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
17 does hereby urge and request Louisiana Economic Development to work with the city of
18 New Orleans, New Orleans & Company, and GNO, Inc. to study and report on the
19 governance, jurisdiction, duties, coordination, public-benefit obligations of boards,
20 commissions, districts, authorities, and related public or quasi-public entities operating on,
21 adjacent to, or materially affecting the riverfront in Orleans Parish.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the study shall include but not be limited to the
23 following:
24 (1) An inventory of boards, commissions, districts, authorities, public benefit entities,
25 nonprofit public instrumentalities, special taxing districts, and other public or quasi-public
26 bodies with jurisdiction, authority, operational responsibility, ownership, management
27 responsibility, taxing authority, financing authority, leasing authority, maintenance duties,
28 programming responsibilities, or other material influence over property, facilities,
29 improvements, operations, public access, or development on, adjacent to, or materially
30 affecting the riverfront in Orleans Parish.
