2 charter, ordinance, contractual, cooperative endeavor, intergovernmental, or other authority.
3 (3) Identification of the geographic boundaries, service areas, or functional
4 jurisdiction of each entity.
5 (4) Identification of the governing structure of each entity, including board
6 composition, appointing authority, reporting obligations, and lines of oversight or
7 accountability.
8 (5) Identification of the assets, facilities, public spaces, improvements, leases, or
9 projects under the authority, ownership, management, control, or material influence of each
10 entity and revenues and financing mechanisms associated with each entity.
11 (6) Evaluation of opportunities to improve coordination, alignment of
12 responsibilities, and clarity of roles among entities, including where multiple entities may
13 operate within the same geography or serve related public purposes.
14 (7) Evaluation of whether public obligations are clearly assigned, including
15 obligations related to public access, maintenance, capital improvements, infrastructure
16 coordination, redevelopment, economic development, neighborhood impacts, public safety,
17 and whether the relationship between basic municipal services and enhanced services is
18 clearly defined and effectively coordinated.
19 (8) Evaluation of land management practices, roles, and responsibilities and
20 coordination across entities and whether existing revenues and responsibilities are aligned
21 for sustainable stewardship of the area, aligned to further leverage and attract private
22 investment for improving and expanding public access and economic development in the
23 area.
24 (9) Identification of any entity, agreement, or financing structure for which enhanced
25 coordination, reporting, or potential statutory or administrative adjustments may be
26 beneficial.
27 (10) Recommendations for any legislation, local ordinances, cooperative endeavor
28 agreements, memoranda of understanding, governance protocols, to improve delivery,
29 efficiency, coordination, fiscal accountability, and public-benefit alignment, including
30 clarifying and strengthening the alignment between basic municipal services and enhanced
