2 (11) Evaluation of the provision of core or basic municipal services delivered by the
3 city of New Orleans, including but not limited to sanitation, public safety, infrastructure
4 maintenance, and code enforcement, and an assessment of how enhanced services, including
5 supplemental cleaning, public space management, security, beautification, programming,
6 and economic development activities provided by districts, authorities, and other public or
7 quasi-public entities are aligned, coordinated, and complementary to basic services.
8 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that, in conducting the study, Louisiana Economic
9 Development may solicit information, cooperation, comments, records, and
10 recommendations from all relevant stakeholders with assets or jurisdictional or operational
11 authority on or near the riverfront and adjacent neighborhoods and districts in Orleans
12 Parish.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that all state agencies, political subdivisions, boards,
14 commissions, districts, authorities, public bodies, and public officials are urged to cooperate
15 with Louisiana Economic Development and to provide information and assistance necessary
16 to carry out the purposes of this Resolution.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that Louisiana Economic Development shall submit
18 a written report of its findings and recommendations to the Legislature of Louisiana and the
19 David R. Poynter Legislative Research Library as required by R.S. 24:772 not later than
20 February 1, 2027.
21 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
22 secretary of Louisiana Economic Development.
